'''Petrivka''' ({{lang-uk|Петрівка}}) is a neighborhood located in the [[Obolonskyi District]] ([[Raions of Ukraine|district]]) of [[Kyiv]], the capital of [[Ukraine]]. It is located in the northern part of the city, neighboring the historical neighborhood of the [[Podil]] itself to its south.

[[File:Moskovskyi Avenue in Kiev 02.JPG|thumb|left|Prospect Stepana Bandery (formerly Moskovsky prospect)]]

One of the city's largest book markets is located in the neighborhood. Petrivka is served by a [[Pochaina (Kiev Metro)|Pochaina metro station]] of the [[Kyiv Metro]]'s [[Obolonsko–Teremkivska Line]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Livoberezhna|url=http://www.metro.kiev.ua/node/166|work=[[Kyiv Metro|Kyiv Metropoliten]]|accessdate=30 April 2014|language=Ukrainian}}</ref> and the [[Pochaina Railway Station]] of the [[Ukrainian Railways|Ukrzaliznytsia]].
